iven name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Heinrich Albaum was born on 27 November 1575, in Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany, his father, Johann Albaum, was 35 and his mother, Elisabeth Doscher, was 35. He married Clara Gillissen in 1600, in Bödefeld, Schmallenberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1650, in his hometown, at the age of 75."},"et":{"27 November 1575–1650":"27. november 1575–1650","1575–1650":"1575–1650","1578–1678":"1578–1678","1620–1672":"1620–1672","1540–1618":"1540–1618","1540–Female":"1540–Surnud","1678":"1678","1600":"1600","1578":"1578","1620":"1620","1575":"1575","1650":"1650","1540":"1540","1672":"1672","27 November 1575":"27. november 1575","1618":"1618","Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Deutschland":"Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa","Bödefeld, Schmallenberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany":"Bödefeld, Schmallenberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa","Altenfeld, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Germany":"Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"27 November 1575–1650":"27. marraskuuta 1575–1650","1575–1650":"1575–1650","1578–1678":"1578–1678","1620–1672":"1620–1672","1540–1618":"1540–1618","1540–Female":"1540–Kuollut","1678":"1678","1600":"1600","1578":"1578","1620":"1620","1575":"1575","1650":"1650","1540":"1540","1672":"1672","27 November 1575":"27. marraskuuta 1575"